Docs.summary: Provides an immutable, read-only set optimized for fast lookup and enumeration.
Docs.remarks: is immutable and is optimized for situations where a set is created infrequently but is used frequently at run time. It has a relatively high cost to create but provides excellent lookup performance. Thus, it is ideal for cases where a set is created once, potentially at the startup of an application, and is used throughout the remainder of the life of the application. should only be initialized with trusted elements, as the details of the elements impacts construction time.
